        <poem>
            <line>Practical man,</line>
            <line>He said, Train your head,</line>
            <line>Your heart, <underlined lineAmnt="single">and your hand.</underlined></line>
            <line>Your fate is here</line>
            <line>And not afar,</line>
            <line>
                <said by="Booker-T-Washington">So let down your bucket</said>
            </line>
            <line>
                <said by="Booker-T-Washington">Where you are.</said>
            </line>
        </poem>
